ILL.md:46:   - Every library listed in the body should correspond to an `index.json` diff.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:56:5. Review each changed `index.json`.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:57:   - Confirm the new versions were added under the correct `metadata-version` entry.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:60:   - For pre-release promotions, confirm `metadata-version` moved from the matching pre-release to the corresponding full release, old pre-release values were removed from `tested-versions`, and any `test-version` references were updated only when they pointed at the promoted test directory.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:65:   - For pre-release promotions, verify the `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` values were rendered from the old version to the promoted `metadata-version` or otherwise corrected to an exact-version URL. Do not accept stale URLs that still point at the old pre-release.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:91:- The PR is limited to the expected `metadata/**/index.json` files.\n./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:92:- Or the PR is a pure verified pre-release promotion rename limited to the matching `metadata/`, `tests/src/`, `stats/`, and `index.json` changes.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:15: * Index entry for metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:23:        @JsonProperty(\"metadata-version\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:39:        @JsonProperty(\"tested-versions\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/model/MetadataVersionsIndexEntry.java:43:        @JsonProperty(\"allowed-packages\")\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect runtime-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, dependency adjustments, runtime configuration, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:31:   - Identify the target coordinate, the previous tested version, and the new tested version from the PR body, title, changed `index.json`, and changed test path.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:37:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Compare `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<old-metadata-version>/stats.json` and `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-metadata-version>/stats.json` when stats files are present in the PR or available on the branch.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:94:Each artifact directory **must** include an `index.json` file (at `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`). This file is a JSON array of objects where each entry describes a specific metadata release.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:99:* `metadata-version`: Specifies the subdirectory where the GraalVM configuration files (e.g., `reflect-config.json`) reside.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:100:* `tested-versions`: An array of library versions verified to work with this specific metadata.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:101:* `allowed-packages`: An array of package prefixes. The TCK ensures that configuration entries (like reflection targets) belong strictly to these packages.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:106:* `default-for`: A Java-format regex used to match library versions if no exact match exists in `tested-versions` (e.g., `\"0\\\\.0\\\\..*\"`).\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:108:* `source-code-url`: URL to the metadata source code location for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:110:* `test-code-url`: URL to the test source code location for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:111:* `documentation-url`: URL to the project documentation for this index entry. Use `$version$` as the placeholder for this entry's `metadata-version` in versioned URLs.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:121:    \"allowed-packages\": [\"org.example.library\"],\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:122:    \"metadata-version\": \"1.0.0\",\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:123:    \"tested-versions\": [\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:137:     \"allowed-packages\": [\"org.example.library\"],\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:138:     \"metadata-version\": \"1.1.0\",\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:144:     \"tested-versions\": [\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:155:To populate `source-code-url`, `repository-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `description` fields in matching `index.json` entries:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:208:This path can be overridden to allow multiple metadata versions to share the same set of test code. This mapping is handled by the local metadata index file (`metadata/<group_id>/<artifact_id>/index.json`).\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect compile-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, imports, renamed APIs, dependency adjustments, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:31:   - Identify the target coordinate, the previous tested version, and the new tested version from the PR body, title, changed `index.json`, and changed test path.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:37:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:55:   - Compare `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<old-metadata-version>/stats.json` and `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-metadata-version>/stats.json` when stats files are present in the PR or available on the branch.\n./docs/support/index.html:561:        return `${rawBaseUrl}/metadata/${encodeURIComponent(group)}/${encodeURIComponent(artifact)}/index.json`;\n./docs/support/index.html:583:          for (const version of entry[\"tested-versions\"] || []) {\n./docs/support/index.html:586:          if (entry[\"metadata-version\"]) {\n./docs/support/index.html:587:            versions.add(entry[\"metadata-version\"]);\n./docs/support/index.html:649:            metadataValue(\"Latest metadata\", latest[\"metadata-version\"]),\n./docs/support/index.html:666:            metadataValue(\"Metadata version\", latest[\"metadata-version\"]),\n./docs/support/index.html:667:            metadataValue(\"Allowed packages\", (latest[\"allowed-packages\"] || []).join(\", \"))\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Require reported dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover. Use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` when available, and block the PR when dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower or the PR provides no credible dynamic-access coverage evidence for non-zero dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:39:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` alone to argue that the submitted metadata is unnecessary.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:43:- A directory tree under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:44:- An artifact-level `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` that records, per metadata version: tested library versions, allowed packages, source/test/documentation URLs, optional `requires`, `default-for`, `skipped-versions`, and `override` flags.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:53:- Validation that every metadata entry uses `typeReachable` and stays inside `allowed-packages`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:136:    Repo->>Artifact: package metadata/** + index.json files\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:141:    Artifact-->>NBT: metadata + index.json per artifact\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:142:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:159:<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json                        # one per supported artifact (element 2)\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:160:<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:164:Plugin-relevant content is `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` and the per-version `reachability-metadata.json` files; the plugin discovers libraries by directory walk. `library-and-framework-list.json` and `schemas/` are present for downstream tooling (the libraries-and-frameworks page and offline validators) and are not consumed by native-build-tools at native-image time.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:166:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\"<group>:<artifact>\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:170:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:172:**4. Version-selection algorithm.** Given an application dependency `g:a:v`, native-build-tools loads the `index.json` array of `g/a/` and applies a primary lookup, picking the first entry that matches in this order:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:174:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:181:    Start([\"Application dependency<br/>g:a:v\"]) --> LoadIndex[\"Load <code>g/a/index.json</code><br/>(array of entries)\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:182:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\"}\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:183:    Tested -- yes --> UseTested[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:185:    DefaultFor -- yes --> UseDefault[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:189:    Latest -- yes --> UseLatest[\"Use that entry's<br/><code>metadata-version/</code>\"]\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:208:- **FR-M-3** Every metadata entry's `typeReachable` condition must reference a class inside the artifact's `allowed-packages`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:210:- **FR-M-5** Each `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/` directory must include a valid `index.json` enumerating its metadata versions and tested library versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:211:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:217:- **FR-T-2** Tests live under `tests/src/<group>/<artifact>/<version>` unless an `index.json` entry sets `test-version` to share a suite across versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:221:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:271:- An `index.json` describing metadata versions and tested versions.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:276:- Validated metadata + tests + index.json under `metadata/` and `tests/src/`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:30:   - Identify the target coordinate, the previous tested version, and the new tested version from the PR body, title, changed `index.json`, metadata path, and test path.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:36:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:54:   - Compare `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<old-metadata-version>/stats.json` and `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<new-metadata-version>/stats.json` when stats files are present in the PR or available on the branch.\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, includes newly added tested versions from artifact-level index diffs, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/). It commits the generated [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) back to the source branch, including links from versions to artifact index files and from coverage values to artifact stats directories, then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `COVERAGE.md`, `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./skills/README.md:17:It encodes the historical approve/close/rerun logic for bulk tested-version updates, checks that the diff stays limited to `metadata/**/index.json`, requires `REQUEST_CHANGES` whenever the review leaves a blocking comment, and approves clean PRs without merging them yet.\n./docs/REVIEWING.md:63:To run these checks automatically, the artifact-level index file at `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json` must include `allowed-packages` properly set ([see this](CONTRIBUTING.md#metadata-structure)).\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/FetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersionsTask.java:174:            File indexFile = new File(\"metadata/\" + group + \"/\" + artifact + \"/index.json\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/FetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersionsTask.java:202:            File coordinatesMetadataIndex = new File(\"metadata/\" + group + \"/\" + artifac